ization subproblem is solved more inexactly. Numerical results show that\nthe significant performance gains achieved by the proposed three designs\nagainst benchmark schemes. Moreover, the inexact-alternating-optimization\ndesigns outperform the exact-alternating-optimization one in terms of both the\nachieved min-weighted-SINR value and the computational complexity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 28 Feb 2020 02:49:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 23 Oct 2020 01:45:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-26"}
